      "writtenOn": "2017-03-27T16:51:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what if for some reason someone calls public function with an empty string? would it break the code and stop the service thread?\nPipe can easily split a transmission into two, e.g. passing the last \\0 byte as a separate buffer - which would become an empty string here\nTheoretically you could use a GUID in a string to make sure you stop marker is unique. But for a better code I\u0027d prefer to have a struct { enum Command; String data } here with command being either NewData or Stop\n\nMessageChannel also got a stop() method that just stops processing immediately, discarding all unprocessed items. That could also work if it\u0027s OK to lose some updates when stopping",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 65,
        "startChar": 37,
