    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ddaa24c3_48e8ea96",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/PropertyWaiter.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-27T16:51:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this interface encourages us having blocked waiting threads, and emulator already routinely creates 100+. What about a callback that\u0027s called when the property arrives? Something like:\n\nPropertyWaiter waiter(\"key\", \"val\", [this](string key, string val) { handlePropertyChange(key, val); });\nPropertyStore::get()-\u003eaddPropertyWaiter(waiter);\n\nThis way it\u0027s possible to implement a synchronous waiter on top (just adding the code from this CL into the callback), or handle property immediately in the callback without blocking a thread.\n\nAlso, if you add a \"bool oneTime\" parameter to addPropertyWaiter() - or allow a callback to return value if it wants to be rescheduled or removed from a waiting list, that would allow for a more efficient code that doesn\u0027t need to remove/add back itself every time if it needs to monitor all changes",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 48,
        "endChar": 37
      },
